# Foodooza Migration Plan
## Phase 1 in This Repo

This repository started as a produce-ordering assessment app. It is now being migrated toward a Foodooza-style food delivery platform in staged phases so the codebase stays runnable while features expand.

## What Is Implemented Now

- Multi-role user foundation on the backend: `user`, `restaurant`, `delivery`, `admin`
- Cookie + bearer-token compatible auth middleware
- New food-delivery domain models:
  - `Shop`
  - `Item`
  - upgraded `Order`
- Public shop discovery endpoints
- Public featured item endpoints
- Shop detail endpoint with menu items
- Customer checkout endpoint with:
  - single-shop cart
  - address capture
  - payment method capture
  - optional scheduling field
- Seed script with sample restaurants and dishes
- Web customer slice:
  - Foodooza landing page
  - featured restaurants
  - featured dishes
  - restaurant menu page
  - local cart
  - checkout page
  - upgraded orders page
  - refreshed Foodooza-style UI

## Next Planned Phases

### Phase 2

- Restaurant dashboard
- Menu CRUD
- Restaurant order management
- Busy mode
- Role-aware onboarding

### Phase 3

- Delivery dashboard
- Assignment flow
- Live location updates
- OTP delivery confirmation
- Earnings analytics

### Phase 4

- Admin moderation dashboard
- User/shop/item/order controls
- Suspensions
- Role switching tools

### Phase 5

- Wallet and refunds
- Coupons
- Notifications
- Reviews and ratings
- Real-time order tracking
- Search autocomplete
- Payments

## Important Constraint

The original repo architecture is still a hybrid monorepo with:

- `backend`
- `web` (Next.js)
- `mobile` (Expo)

The current migration focuses on building a strong Foodooza domain foundation first, then expanding dashboard and real-time features incrementally instead of attempting a risky full rewrite in one pass.
